			<ns0:name>arben...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/115623601907745403448/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Currently, pre-reserved address space is detected on POSIX systems by looking at a global variable that is set on the Chrome side (see chrome/nacl/nacl_helper_linux.cc).  Because of this, standalone sel_ldr nacl tests on linux cannot detect pre-reserved address space.  Subsequently, our testing capabilities are limited.

We can pass arguments from nacl to chrome via the NaClChromeMainArgs data structure and NaClChromeMainArgsCreate().  The plan is to use command-line arguments on the nacl side to specify the pre-reserved address space.  This will require updates to nacl_bootstrap.
